## MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)

**Concept:** MVVM is an evolution of MVC, particularly popular in UI frameworks that support data binding (e.g., Angular, Vue, React with hooks/state management). It introduces a **ViewModel**.

*   **Model:** Same as in MVC – data and business logic.
*   **View:** The UI. It's more active than in MVC, as it typically binds directly to properties and commands exposed by the ViewModel. The View largely observes the ViewModel.
*   **ViewModel:** An abstraction of the View. It exposes data and commands that the View can bind to. It contains presentation logic (how the data should be displayed) and acts as a data binder between the Model and the View. It transforms Model data into View-friendly properties and handles user input by delegating to the Model. It does *not* have a direct reference to the View.

**Data Flow:** Bidirectional data binding between View and ViewModel, but the primary flow for state changes is:
`User Input -> View -> ViewModel -> Model -> ViewModel -> View (via data binding)`

**Diagram:**

```
[User] <--> [View] <--> [ViewModel] <--> [Model]
             (Data Binding)
```

**Practical Use Cases:**
*   Modern front-end frameworks (Angular, Vue.js, React (conceptually, though React's component model is often simpler)).
*   WPF, Silverlight, UWP (where it originated).

**Trade-offs:**
*   **Pros:** Excellent for UI frameworks with data binding, enhances testability (ViewModel can be tested independently of the UI), reduces boilerplate code in the View, better separation of UI logic from business logic.
*   **Cons:** Can introduce complexity with data binding mechanisms, ViewModel can become large if not managed properly, learning curve for data binding concepts.

**Example (Simplified, using a conceptual binding):**

```typescript
// Model (same as MVC)
class UserData {
    private _name: string;
    private _email: string;
    private observers: Function[] = [];

    constructor(name: string, email: string) {
        this._name = name;
        this._email = email;
    }

    get name(): string { return this._name; }
    get email(): string { return this._email; }

    setName(newName: string) {
        this._name = newName;
        this.notifyObservers();
    }

    setEmail(newEmail: string) {
        this._email = newEmail;
        this.notifyObservers();
    }

    addObserver(observer: Function) {
        this.observers.push(observer);
    }

    private notifyObservers() {
        this.observers.forEach(observer => observer());
    }
}

// ViewModel
class UserViewModel {
    private model: UserData;
    public displayName: string = '';
    public displayEmail: string = '';
    private onUpdateCallbacks: Function[] = []; // To simulate observable properties

    constructor(model: UserData) {
        this.model = model;
        this.model.addObserver(() => this.updateViewModelFromModel());
        this.updateViewModelFromModel(); // Initial sync
    }

    private updateViewModelFromModel() {
        // Transform model data for display
        this.displayName = this.model.name.toUpperCase(); // Presentation logic
        this.displayEmail = `Contact: ${this.model.email}`;
        this.notifyUpdate();
    }

    public updateName(newName: string) {
        this.model.setName(newName); // Delegate to Model
    }

    public updateEmail(newEmail: string) {
        this.model.setEmail(newEmail); // Delegate to Model
    }

    // Simulate observable property updates for the View
    public addUpdateCallback(callback: Function) {
        this.onUpdateCallbacks.push(callback);
    }

    private notifyUpdate() {
        this.onUpdateCallbacks.forEach(cb => cb());
    }
}

// View (React-like component for demonstration of binding)
class UserDisplayComponent {
    private viewModel: UserViewModel;
    private element: HTMLElement;

    constructor(viewModel: UserViewModel, elementId: string) {
        this.viewModel = viewModel;
        this.element = document.getElementById(elementId)!;

        // Bind View to ViewModel updates
        this.viewModel.addUpdateCallback(() => this.render());
        this.render(); // Initial render
    }

    render() {
        this.element.innerHTML = `
            <h3>${this.viewModel.displayName}</h3>
            <p>${this.viewModel.displayEmail}</p>
            <input type="text" id="nameInput" value="${this.viewModel.displayName.toLowerCase()}"/>
            <button id="updateNameBtn">Update Name</button>
        `;

        // Simulate two-way binding for input
        this.element.querySelector('#updateNameBtn')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const newName = (this.element.querySelector('#nameInput') as HTMLInputElement).value;
            this.viewModel.updateName(newName);
        });
    }
}

// // Usage:
// const userModelMVVM = new UserData('Bob', 'bob@example.com');
// const userViewModel = new UserViewModel(userModelMVVM);
// const userComponent = new UserDisplayComponent(userViewModel, 'app-mvvm');

// // Simulating external change to model (e.g., from an API)
// setTimeout(() => userModelMVVM.setName('Robert Smith'), 3000);
```

